    <fr:title text="Closed set">Closed set</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>We define a subset of a given set to be <html:em>closed</html:em> under some operation on the larget set if preforming that operation on a member of the <html:em>subset</html:em> always produces a member of the same subset. Formally we can say that:</html:p>
    <html:ul><html:li>Given some <html:strong>set operation</html:strong> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : X^n \to  X]]></fr:tex></html:li>
  <html:li>A subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S \subseteq  X]]></fr:tex> is <html:strong>closed</html:strong> under the operation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> if
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
      \forall  x_1, x_2, \ldots , x_n \in  S.\ f(x_1, x_2, \ldots , x_n) \in  S
    ]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ul>
  </fr:mainmatter>
